            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3673987-lost-planet-airman?shelf=completed-series">completed-series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3673987-lost-planet-airman?shelf=challenge-a-a-2017">challenge-a-a-2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1950108751" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18145373505316531158">Fits nicely into what I remember of the Tripods trilogy. <br/>But that is as-expected; it should, and does, dovetail -- the author wrote it to inform his readership, and answer the nay-sayers, that the human race could fall to the mind control technology of an alien race -- and yes, it could happen like this, witha deceptive feint into our military strengths and the hidden knife slipping into the chinks in our technology and to our selfish desire for entertainment.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


