<div id="review_118542610" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/118542610" />
    <a title="Rebecca Radnor" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3888589-rebecca-radnor"><img alt="Rebecca Radnor" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1294010997p2/3888589.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/118542610?book_show_action=true">Aug 25, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rebecca Radnor" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rebecca Radnor" href="/user/show/3888589-rebecca-radnor">Rebecca Radnor</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3888589-rebecca-radnor?shelf=ya-not-historical">ya-not-historical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3888589-rebecca-radnor?shelf=sf-science-fiction-and-fantacy">sf-science-fiction-and-fantacy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer118542610" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer77676234865307320">Prequel to the Scifi series that introduced me to Scifi, when I was like 8 or 9 (40 years ago). It&apos;s a very short read, well written and kind of terrifying. The invasion of humanity happens very matter of factually. As you&apos;re reading it, it all makes so much sense -- and in retrospect you can see its likelihood (assuming any alien race were ever to try to invade us).<br/><br/>That said, read the trilogy first, then read this one.... the order as written, and please remember it&apos;s aimed at kids who are too </span>
  <span id="freeText77676234865307320" style="display:none">Prequel to the Scifi series that introduced me to Scifi, when I was like 8 or 9 (40 years ago). It's a very short read, well written and kind of terrifying. The invasion of humanity happens very matter of factually. As you're reading it, it all makes so much sense -- and in retrospect you can see its likelihood (assuming any alien race were ever to try to invade us).<br /><br />That said, read the trilogy first, then read this one.... the order as written, and please remember it's aimed at kids who are too old for kids' books but maybe don't have the reading skills yet for adult fiction. But, that said, if you have young readers at home (of about 8 or 9 years old) who like SciFi movies, it's a good series to introduce them to. </span>
  <a data-text-id="77676234865307320" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


