        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3785803321" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13523078020585777944">3.5 stars. A solid prequel to the <i>Tripods</i> trilogy that traces the roots of humans coming under the control of the alien Tripods. The scenario is believable and frightening, with a gradual separation of society into those &quot;in the know&quot; and the dehumanization of all others. Characters are believable and very relatable for a young adult audience. Quick read that could stand alone, but is more a story that enhances the main trilogy.</span>
  <span id="freeText13523078020585777944" style="display:none">3.5 stars. A solid prequel to the <i>Tripods</i> trilogy that traces the roots of humans coming under the control of the alien Tripods. The scenario is believable and frightening, with a gradual separation of society into those "in the know" and the dehumanization of all others. Characters are believable and very relatable for a young adult audience. Quick read that could stand alone, but is more a story that enhances the main trilogy.</span>
